main event: A report of a satellite-like object was observed on 17 May 1964.
interesting points: The observation lasted approximately 5 minutes., The object was at 45 degrees elevation and 252 degrees azimuth initially., The object faded from view at 50 degrees elevation and 010 degrees azimuth., The report was part of Project Blue Book documentation., It was analyzed by multiple military branches including the Air Force and Navy.
